title: error compiling a warp project

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code

```Rust
use std::sync::Arc;

use bytes::Bytes;
use warp::{Filter, Rejection, Reply};

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() {
    let handler = Arc::new(NotariusHttpHandler {});
    let lambda = move |bytes| inner_handle_sign(handler.clone(), bytes);

    let sign = warp::post()
        .and(warp::body::bytes())
        .and_then(lambda);
    warp::serve(sign).run(([0, 0, 0, 0], 3030)).await;
}

fn inner_handle_sign(
    handler: Arc<NotariusHttpHandler>,
    bytes: Bytes,
) -> Result<impl Reply, Rejection> {
    handler.handle_sign(bytes)
}

pub struct NotariusHttpHandler {}

impl NotariusHttpHandler {
    pub async fn handle_sign(&self, _bytes: Bytes) -> Result<impl Reply, Rejection> {
        loop {}
    }
}
```
